Taxonomy Codes for Obstetricians and Gynecologists

Source: R/taxonomy.R
taxonomy.Rd

This dataset contains taxonomy codes for Obstetricians and Gynecologists among other healthcare providers.

Usage

taxonomy

Format

A data frame with two columns:

NUCC Code

NUCC (National Uniform Claim Committee) code for healthcare providers.

Provider Type

The type of healthcare provider corresponding to the NUCC code.

Source

https://www.nucc.org/images/stories/PDF/taxonomy_23_0.pdf

Value

A tibble mapping NUCC taxonomy codes to descriptive provider types relevant to obstetrics and gynecology research.

See also

Other datasets: ACOG_Districts, acgme, cityStateToLatLong, fips

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Load the taxonomy dataset
data(taxonomy)

# Explore the dataset
print(taxonomy)
} # }
